Prefer const, enums and inlines to #define:


#define ASPECT_RATION 1.65

better way is const double ASPECT_RATIo = 1.63

because constants is seen to compilers - defines not so it is easiest to recognize compile errors with constants instead of define.


Pointers also better to be constants with data to:

const char * const ch = "asdad";

Or better use strings:

const std::string ch = String("AAA");


DEFINES use only for macroses (Хотя я бы поставил под сомнение вообще использование макросов)
